<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="526" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="129.[156,1364,292,959]" pageId="129" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[158,504,725,758]" pageId="129" pageNumber="526">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCNRed List. The Mamfe White-toothed Shrew might be threatened by deforestation from logging and land conversion, although virtually nothing is known aboutits natural history and population status.
</paragraph>
